column1: This spreadsheet lists the metadata for ongoing observations for Grade A projects in 12m and Grade A and B in ACA only that are in the observing queue as of 2020 March 9.

column3: Description
ALMA Project code.
Name of the science target.
Target right ascension, in decimal degrees (0 for solar system targets).
Target declination, in decimal degress (0 for solar system targets).
Target right ascension, in Hr,Min,Sec.
Target declination, in Deg, Min, Sec.
Right Ascension/galactic-longitude offset in arcsec. Offset is in RA unless Mos.Coord.Ref.Sys is "galactic".
Declination/galactic-latitude offset in arcsec. Offset is in declination unless Mos.Coord.Ref.Sys is "galactic".
Target velocity
Target velocity reference frame.
Velocity convention (radio, optical, or relativistic).
Type of mosaic, either Rectangle, Custom, or N/A; N/A implies there is a single pointing for the target.
If a rectangular mosaic was requested: Length of rectangular area to be mapped as defined in the ALMA Observing Tool (OT).
If a rectangular mosaic was requested: Width of rectangular area to be mapped as defined in the ALMA Observing Tool (OT).
If a rectangular mosaic was requested: Position Angle of rectangular area to be mapped as defined in the ALMA Observing Tool (OT).
If a rectangular mosaic was requested: Spacing betweeng pointings.
If the target is a mosaic, this field gives the coordinate system sed to define the mosaic.
ALMA Observing Band, in format "ALMA_RB" followed by Band ID.
Requested angular resolution
Requested largest angular scale
Indicates if  observations with ACA 7-m Array are requested.
Indicates if observations with ACA Total Power Array are requested.
Indicates if observations are ACA 7-m Array only.
Polarization products: Full, Dual or Single-X.
Reference frequency for user-requested sensitivity.
Reference bandwidth for user-requested sensitivity.
Indicates if the frequencies for the spectral scan and spectral windows  are sky frequencies; If False,  the frequencies represent rest frequencies.
If the observation is a spectral scan: Start frequency of the spectral scan.
If the observation is a spectral scan: End frequency of the spectral scan.
If the observation is a spectral scan: bandwidth of each window in the spectral scan.
If the observation is a spectral scan: spectral resolution of the spectral scan.
Central  frequency in GHz for Spectral Window #N (where N = 1-16).
Bandwidth of spectral window #N (where N= 1-16).
Spectral resolution spectral Window #N (where N = 1-16).
RA
[deg]
